procedures.name: Blood Sampling
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, and pregnancy testing.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour collection for copper and molybdenum measurement.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full or symptom-driven physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Recording of the heart's electrical activity, performed in triplicate at specified timepoints.

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Oral Administration of ALXN1840
procedures.label: Drug Administration
procedures.description: Oral administration of ALXN1840 tablets once daily.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine or serum pregnancy testing for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Urinalysis
procedures.label: Urinalysis
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis of a urine sample.

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent for bilirubin, glucose, hemoglobin, ketones, leukocytes, nitrite, pH, protein, specific gravity, urobilinogen, any number of these constituents; automated, with microscopy

procedures.name: Clinical Safety Laboratory Assessments
procedures.label: Safety Labs
procedures.description: Blood tests including serum chemistry, hematology, and coagulation panels.

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurement
procedures.label: Height/Weight/BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of participant's height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Collection and follow-up of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs) throughout the study.

procedures.name: Intravenous Cannula Placement
procedures.label: IV Cannula Placement
procedures.description: Placement of an intravenous cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Monitoring
procedures.label: Bowel/Urine Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring and recording of urination and bowel movements.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure and Heart Rate Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A flexible tube placed inside a vein to provide venous access for blood sampling.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometry
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Analytical instrument used to determine copper and molybdenum concentration in biological and dietary samples.
